724755f-b.text:
134-36 and 124-32 White Street, at, adjoining and west of the

724753f-a.title: Manhattan: White Street - Baxter Street
724753f-a.text:
White Street, north side, from Baxter (richt) to Centre (left)
Rtreets, as viewed northward across the cleared site for the new
Criminal Corts (and prison) Bldg. This incorporates two square
blocks which have just been cleared and are bounded by Centre,east
to Baxter, and Leonard, north to White Streets. fhru the center
runs Franklin Street. The photographers vantage point in No. 1
is Leonard Street, while in No.2 he is on Baxter Street. To the
left in the latter instance, is Columbus Park.
June 10, 1938.
View 2: June 12, 1938
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
